426. Aulide = here the Greek fleet assembled for the expe- dition against Troy. Dido means that she was not a foe to Aeneas and his people as the Greeks were.

427. One of the Greeks was said to have taken up the bones of Anchises. To desecrate a grave, or prevent proper burial, was considered by the ancients as a most horrible crime, because it was supposed to prevent the spirit of the dead man finding rest anywhere.
